   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Symbolic derivation of 1-D FEM stiffness matrix"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "42e1456e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First import everything. Note how we now import sympy as sy to make it clear which functions we are using"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "id": "54e23217",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import sympy as sy\n",
    "from scipy.linalg import solve\n",
    "from scipy.sparse import spdiags\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
    "mpl.rcParams['figure.dpi']= 300\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e6da359f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we define the symbols, compute the shape function, and build the stiffness matrix of a single elelemt."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "id": "4ec35471",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/latex": [
       "$\\displaystyle \\left[\\begin{matrix}- \\frac{c}{2} + \\frac{k}{dx} & \\frac{c}{2} - \\frac{k}{dx}\\\\- \\frac{c}{2} - \\frac{k}{dx} & \\frac{c}{2} + \\frac{k}{dx}\\end{matrix}\\right]$"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "Matrix([\n",
       "[-c/2 + k/dx, c/2 - k/dx],\n",
       "[-c/2 - k/dx, c/2 + k/dx]])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 27,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# symbols\n",
    "dx, x, k, xi, c = sy.symbols('dx x k xi c')\n",
    "    \n",
    "N1  = 1-x/(dx)\n",
    "N2  = x/(dx)\n",
    "\n",
    "E11 = sy.simplify(sy.integrate((N1*c*sy.diff(N1,x) + sy.diff(N1,x)*k*sy.diff(N1,x)), ( x, 0, dx)))\n",
    "E12 = sy.simplify(sy.integrate((N1*c*sy.diff(N2,x) + sy.diff(N1,x)*k*sy.diff(N2,x)), ( x, 0, dx))) \n",
    "E21 = sy.simplify(sy.integrate((N2*c*sy.diff(N1,x) + sy.diff(N2,x)*k*sy.diff(N1,x)), ( x, 0, dx))) \n",
    "E22 = sy.simplify(sy.integrate((N2*c*sy.diff(N2,x) + sy.diff(N2,x)*k*sy.diff(N2,x)), ( x, 0, dx)))\n",
    "\n",
    "Ael = sy.Matrix([[E11, E12], [E21, E22]])\n",
    "Ael"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3be90f4a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note how we made a little simplification here and integrated from 0 to dx and not from x(i) to x(i+1); the result is the same.\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we build the global stiffness matrix by adding all element stiffness matrices to the big global stiffness matrix. Unfortunately, the indexing in sympy matrices is a bit different to normal numpy indexing. \n",
    "\n",
    "We there have to use a little trick that is described here:\n",
    "https://www.reddit.com/r/learnpython/comments/f7uxn6/question_how_to_add_matrix_to_submatrix_in_sympy/\n",
    "\n",
    "We simply identify the upper left index on the left-hand side and use list indexing on the right-hand side when adding the small matrices to the big one."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "id": "f2173a93",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/latex": [
       "$\\displaystyle \\left[\\begin{matrix}- \\frac{c}{2} + \\frac{k}{dx} & \\frac{c}{2} - \\frac{k}{dx} & 0 & 0 & 0\\\\- \\frac{c}{2} - \\frac{k}{dx} & \\frac{2 k}{dx} & \\frac{c}{2} - \\frac{k}{dx} & 0 & 0\\\\0 & - \\frac{c}{2} - \\frac{k}{dx} & \\frac{2 k}{dx} & \\frac{c}{2} - \\frac{k}{dx} & 0\\\\0 & 0 & - \\frac{c}{2} - \\frac{k}{dx} & \\frac{2 k}{dx} & \\frac{c}{2} - \\frac{k}{dx}\\\\0 & 0 & 0 & - \\frac{c}{2} - \\frac{k}{dx} & \\frac{c}{2} + \\frac{k}{dx}\\end{matrix}\\right]$"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "Matrix([\n",
       "[-c/2 + k/dx,  c/2 - k/dx,           0,           0,          0],\n",
       "[-c/2 - k/dx,      2*k/dx,  c/2 - k/dx,           0,          0],\n",
       "[          0, -c/2 - k/dx,      2*k/dx,  c/2 - k/dx,          0],\n",
       "[          0,           0, -c/2 - k/dx,      2*k/dx, c/2 - k/dx],\n",
       "[          0,           0,           0, -c/2 - k/dx, c/2 + k/dx]])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 24,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# numerical paramters\n",
    "nel     = 4       # number of elements\n",
    "nnodel  = 2       # nodes per element \n",
    "nnod    = nel+1   # number of nodes\n",
    "\n",
    "EL2NOD  = np.array([np.arange(1,nnod), np.arange(2,nnod+1)])  # connectivity matrix\n",
    "\n",
    "# global matrix assemly\n",
    "A = sy.zeros(nnod, nnod)\n",
    "for iel in range(0,4):\n",
    "    A[EL2NOD[0,iel]-1,EL2NOD[0,iel]-1] = A[list(EL2NOD[:,iel]-1), list(EL2NOD[:,iel]-1)] + Ael\n",
    "\n",
    "A\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9c6a6ff5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Does this matrix look familiar? Compare it to the FTCS solution - it's the same safe for a constant factor dx, which drops out because I also shows up on the RHS (if we had one)!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "33610fc6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ok let's implement it and compare it to the analytical solution!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "c3a879b2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<function matplotlib.pyplot.show(close=None, block=None)>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 26,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 3000x1500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# model parameters\n",
    "c       = 20\n",
    "k       = 2\n",
    "nx      = 11\n",
    "x0      = 0\n",
    "x1      = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "Tleft   = 0\n",
    "Tright  = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "X,dx    = np.linspace(x0,x1, nx, retstep=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "#peclet number for stability analysis\n",
    "peclet  = c*dx/(2*k)\n",
    "\n",
    "#analytical solution with boundary conditions T(0) = 0 and T(1) = 1;\n",
    "C2      = 1/(1-np.exp(c/k))\n",
    "C1      = -C2;\n",
    "Tana    = C1*np.exp(c/k*X) + C2\n",
    "\n",
    "# FEM solution\n",
    "# build the coefficient matrix\n",
    "data  = (np.ones((nx,1))*np.array([-(c/(2) + k/dx), (2*k/dx), -(-c/(2)+k/dx) ])).T\n",
    "diags = np.array([-1, 0, 1])\n",
    "A     = spdiags(data, diags, nx, nx).toarray()\n",
    "\n",
    "# and add boundary conditions\n",
    "A[0,0]       = 1\n",
    "A[0,1]       = 0\n",
    "A[nx-1,nx-1] = 1\n",
    "A[nx-1,nx-2] = 0\n",
    "Rhs          = np.zeros(nx)\n",
    "Rhs[0]       = Tleft\n",
    "Rhs[-1]       = Tright\n",
    "Tfem=solve(A,Rhs)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# plot everything\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n",
    "fig.clf()\n",
    "ax  = plt.axes(xlim=(x0, x1), ylim=(Tleft, Tright))\n",
    "line, = ax.plot([], [], lw=1)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Distance')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Temperature')\n",
    "plt.plot(X, Tana, label='Analytical solution')\n",
    "plt.plot(X, Tfem, label='FEM')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  }
